{
  "texts": [
    "Weighted MaxCutThe proposed procedure is as follows.",
    "First, rescale the edge weights in the graph followingw uv → w uv 1 |E| {u,v}∈E w 2 uv.",
    "(6)Second, use the parameter setting rule for the corresponding unweighted graph.As an example of parameter setting rule for unweighted graphs to be used in the second step, one can use the parameters β inf, γ inf optimized for large-girth regular graphs in the infinite-size limit [7, Tables 4 and 5] and follow the rescaling procedure therein, which we include here for completeness:β = β inf, γ = γ inf / √ D.Here D is the average degree of the graph.",
    "Alternatively, the procedure from Ref.",
    "[38] can be used."
  ]
}